      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a pristine FD3S RX-7, a masterclass in lightweight engineering. The 13B-REW power plant retains its factory-spec sequential turbocharger configuration, delivering a linear torque curve without the boost lag typical of aftermarket single-turbo conversions. The chassis remains structurally rigid with no evidence of fatigue, supported by the original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and aluminum control arms. Power is transmitted through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal traction. This example features a flawless exterior finish and a cockpit devoid of common plastics degradation. All vacuum lines have been meticulously inspected, and the apex seals maintain factory-standard compression levels. A true collector-grade specimen for the rotary purist.",
